Reasoning: The paper deals with Bayesian estimation of probability of success in a series of trials with binary outcomes, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The study of asymptotic behavior of differential entropy is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of weighted differential entropy is also relevant to information theory and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the application of Rao-Cram\'er, Bhattacharyya and Kullback inequalities is related to statistics (cs.ST).
